{
  "texts": [
    "In this context, the model uses its understanding of previous dialogue to generate relevant and contextually appropriate responses.",
    "Intuition: Fine-tuning tailors the SFT model to the specific nuances of a given task or domain so that it can generalize better on unseen data.",
    "Other advantages of fine-tuning are faster convergence with fewer labeled datasets from a specific domain.",
    "For instance, GPT-1 used 100 passes through the training data for self-supervised pretraining but only 3 passes for supervised finetuning (Brown et al. 2020).",
    "Supervised fine-tuning enables companies to create domain-specific models by using their private or proprietary datasets."
  ]
}